				<div class="ACT"><br><ul><li>For example , Pb ( II ) - , Cd ( II ) - , Zn ( II ) - , and Bi ( III ) - bound CadC proteins have signi cents - cantly decreased a ‚ÅÑ nities ( 340 - , 230 - , 185 - , and 170-fold decrease respectively ) for the DNA compared to the apo-protein [ 23,39,40 ] ; addition of these metal ions to the preformed apo-CadC ^ DNA complex also results in CadC dissociation from the DNA ( M.L. VanZile and D.P. Gie-droc , unpublished results ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12829264" target="_blank">12829264</a>]<br></li>
<li>Recent comparative spectroscopic and functional studies of highly puri cents ed wild-type and ligand substitution mutants of Synechococcus SmtB , S. aureus pI258 CadC , Synechocystis ZiaR , S. aureus CzrA ( M. Pennella , C. Eicken , J. Sacchettini and D.P. Giedroc , manuscript in preparation ) and M. tuberculosis NmtR are consistent with a unifying ` theme and variations ' model for metal binding by this family of proteins .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12829264" target="_blank">12829264</a>]<br></li>
<li>In fact , several repressor proteins in this family do utilize ligands from this ` box ' including ArsR and CadC proteins ; however , it is now known that this parallel can not be made to all other members of the family [ 39,45,46 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12829264" target="_blank">12829264</a>]<br></li>
<li>The O/P binding properties of other members of the SmtB/ArsR family , including the K5C sensor NmtR and the K3N sensor CadC , are also strongly negatively regulated by metal binding .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12829264" target="_blank">12829264</a>]<br></li>
<li>Hsieh , P. F. , Lin , H. H. , Lin , T. L. , and Wang , J. T. ( 2010 ) CadC regulates cad and tdc operons in response to gastrointestinal stresses and enhances intestinal colonization of Klebsiella pneumoniae .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25403562" target="_blank">25403562</a>]<br></li>
<li>Acid induction is mediated by the CadC regulator ( Watson et al. , 1992 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9534244" target="_blank">9534244</a>]<br></li>
<li>( v ) CadC is limiting in the cell for Pcad induction .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1370290" target="_blank">1370290</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although the mechanism of this LysP-mediated repression is not understood , this result led to the suggestions that LysP inhibits the ability of CadC to activate transcription and that lysine , possibly through an interaction with CadC or LysP , eliminates this inhibition ( 11 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8808945" target="_blank">8808945</a>]<br></li>
<li>Neely MN , Dell CL , Olson ER : Roles of LysP and CadC in mediating the lysine requirement for acid induction of the Escherichia coli cad operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21034467" target="_blank">21034467</a>]<br></li>
